OL,3,CMurder in the street: The religious
OL,4,Cextremist's terror attack in Hartlepool
OL,6,F"He took it upon himself to enter the
OL,7,Froom, to cause Mr Nouri harm purely
OL,8,Fbecause of his religious beliefs" -
OL,9,FHead of Counter Terrorism North East,
OL,10,FDetective Chief Superintendent James
OL,11,FDunkerley
OL,13,FBy the time police arrived, Alid had
OL,14,Ffled the house thinking he had
OL,15,Fsuccessfully murdered Mr Nouri.
OL,17,FHowever, he survived after extensive
OL,18,Fsurgery despite stab wounds in the
OL,19,Fchest and leg that left him bleeding
OL,20,Fextensively.
