OL,6,FPaul Crowley continued: "The officers,
OL,7,Fthe way that they acted, the way that
OL,8,Fthey detained the offender without any
OL,9,Ffurther harm being caused, was simply
OL,10,Foutstanding."
OL,12,FAs he was booked in for questioning,
OL,13,FAlid unapologetically made his
OL,14,Fmotivations clear.
OL,16,FThe Judge told today of how Alid
OL,17,F"explained that the issue was the
OL,18,Findependence of Palestine - he had
OL,19,Fkilled two adults in revenge for
OL,20,FIsrael killing innocent people and
OL,21,Fchildren by air strikes".
