OL,6,F"It could be spontaneous, meaning you
OL,7,Fwon't be made aware of when they're
OL,8,Fgoing to attack."
OL,10,F"Alid was hellbent on causing harm
OL,11,Fthat day. Had we not stopped him, we
OL,12,Fwould have had far more fatalities in
OL,13,FHartlepool" - Head of Counter
OL,14,FTerrorism North East, Detective Chief
OL,15,FSuperintendent James Dunkerley
OL,17,FAlid claimed his intentions were to
OL,18,Finfluence Britain's leaders, which the
OL,19,FJudge said were designed to
OL,20,F"intimidate" and "frighten" the people
OL,21,Fof Britain.
